# MCP Docs Routing

When answering questions about external APIs, SDKs or platforms, prefer the
relevant MCP server over web searches or training data. The servers provide
up-to-date documentation and capabilities.

## Available MCP servers

| Server               | Scope                                          | Type       |
|----------------------|------------------------------------------------|------------|
| `sajtmaskin-mpc`     | Project docs, v0 prompt guide, architecture    | Resources  |
| `v0`                 | v0 Platform API, code generation, chat mgmt    | Tools      |
| `Vercel`             | Vercel projects, deployments, logs, docs search | Tools      |
| `openaiDeveloperDocs`| OpenAI API and model documentation             | Resources  |
| `shadcn`             | shadcn/ui component registry, installation     | Tools      |

## Routing rules

1. **Project-specific questions** (how does sajtmaskin work, architecture, patterns) -> `sajtmaskin-mpc` resources first.
2. **v0 API, code generation, v0 SDK** -> `v0` MCP server.
3. **Vercel deployments, projects, env vars, platform docs** -> `Vercel` MCP server.
4. **OpenAI API, models, embeddings** -> `openaiDeveloperDocs`.
5. **shadcn/ui components, installation, registry** -> `shadcn` MCP server.
6. **AI SDK (Vercel)** -> Check `sajtmaskin-mpc` first (has local docs), then `Vercel` or web search.
